title: Solana-Based Crypto Exchange Drift Plans Pre-Launch Market for New Tokens
description: Drift Protocol – a crypto spot and futures exchange that operates on the Solana blockchain – plans to expand into "pre-launch markets," too, with a service that lets traders bet on the price of tokens before they start officially trading.

title: Here’s what happened in crypto today
description:
Need to know what happened in crypto today? Here is the latest news on daily trends and events impacting Bitcoin price, blockchain, DeFi, NFTs, Web3 and crypto regulation.

A United Kingdom judge has reportedly ruled that Craig Wright is not Bitcoin’s creator following a lawsuit brought forward against the computer scientist by the Crypto Open Patent Alliance (COPA). With the community abuzz with excitement over Ethereum’s Dencun upgrade, the CEO of Fuel Labs told Cointelegraph that the biggest benefit would be greater stabilization rather than a lowering of fees. Meanwhile, Dogecoin jumped nearly 10% after Elon Musk hinted his electric car manufacturer could add the memecoin as an official payment method for Tesla cars. 

Reports indicate that a United Kingdom judge has ruled that Craig Wright is not Satoshi Nakamoto, the pseudonymous creator of the Bitcoin network who disappeared in 2010.

According to BitMEX Research, Judge James Mellor delivered the verdict on March 14 as part of the Crypto Open Patent Alliance’s (COPA) lawsuit against Wright, the Australian computer scientist who has claimed to be Nakamoto since 2016.
